In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki introduced FEMA Administrator Deanne Criswell, who provided an update on FEMA's efforts to combat the COVID-19 pandemic. Criswell highlighted FEMA's support in providing medical personnel, personal protective equipment, testing sites, and federal resources to states and local communities. She emphasized the need for medical staffing in hospitals and announced the deployment of additional medical teams to six states. Criswell also announced an expansion of FEMA's policy to allow funding for states to use National Guard troops in critical support roles in hospitals. She highlighted the ongoing coordination with federal partners and the allocation of nearly $100 billion in funding for COVID-related needs. Criswell mentioned the shifting challenges posed by the Delta and Omicron variants and expressed the commitment of the federal government to continue supporting the fight against COVID-19.